categories_genes.explanation: This gene encodes a protein called hypoxia-inducible factor 1-alpha that is an important regulator of the body´s response to hypoxia. When oxygen is lacking, this protein starts the process of making new blood vessels and red blood cells, among other things that will increase oxygen delivery. It is also a regulator of glucose metabolism, a central source of fuel during anaerobic or power-based exercise.

gene_evaluations.explanation: This variation is not linked to a higher VO2 max.
This variation is not linked to a higher VO2 max.
This variation is linked to better endurance performance and VO2 max.

confidence_score.explanation: C is our lowest score. Gene variants and categories with a C grade is usually restricted to a small number of studies including a low number participants. The score C can also reflect that not all studies find a significant effect of the gene variant. However gene variants with this score probably still have an effect and the categories can still provide you with valuable knowledge.

This variation is linked to increased levels of protein production and a high VO2 max potential.
